cs5031.catalogplayer.catalog
Interface Resource

All Known Subinterfaces:
Album, Track
All Known Implementing Classes:
MyAlbum, MyResource, MyTrack
public interface Resource

A resource in an online catalog. A resource has an identifier, a URL where it can be accessed and a type. The latter is an id from the list of ids defined in this interface, so is not specific to the catalog.

Author:
alex.voss@st-andrews.ac.uk

Method Detail

getIdentifier

java.lang.Object getIdentifier()
Get the catalog-specific identifier for the resource. As different catalogs may used different kinds of identifiers and as they are meaningful only in the context of the catalog they relate to, the interface defines a return value of type Object.

Returns:
an Object serving as the identifier for this resource in its catalog

getResourceURL

java.net.URL getResourceURL()
Get a URL under which the metadata about the resource can be accessed.

Returns:
the URL under which the resource metadata can be accessed

getType

int getType()
Get the catalogue independent resource type identifier. This will be one of the values of the constants defined in this interface.

Returns:
the type identifier for this resource
